Cross-domain translation

This also strengthens your Comparative Distillation doctrine.

Instead of asking,

“What is this like?”

ask,

“At what resolution are these two domains structurally equivalent?”

For example:

* An ecosystem and a market are not identical in detail.
* At a coarse level, both involve interacting agents, resource flows, feedback loops, and adaptation.

That coarse representation lets you transfer hypotheses. Then you zoom back in and test them against the details of the target domain. This preserves rigor while still encouraging creative analogies.

