A possible Pantheon invariant

One formulation that fits your architecture is:

Intelligence is the ability to dynamically allocate representational resolution.

An intelligent system does not maximize detail everywhere. It allocates limited attention and computation where they are most valuable, compresses what can safely remain abstract, and shifts resolution as goals and evidence change. The “optimal resolution” becomes a controllable variable rather than a fixed property of the representation itself.

That framing is broad enough to connect perception, reasoning, memory, scientific discovery, engineering design, and AI systems, while remaining grounded as a hypothesis about how adaptive problem-solving can be organized.